metadata.name: Conveying Opulence #29
metadata.description:
"and my dreams are composed either by my mind or by chance" - Italo Calvino, Invisible Cities, 1972 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Take a simple algorithm, arrange basic geometric units by chance, take half of that composition and mirror it, repeat it again and again until opulence is conveyed. 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

The subtle grain effect is done with p5.grain library by @gorillasu & @meezwhite. 

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations.

metadata.name: *pl[ASCii]23 #24
metadata.description:
"ASCII is a fundamental encoding standard that assigns a unique numeric value to each character, allowing computers to exchange text-based information by representing characters as binary data."

In this collection, I took ASCII as the main theme, which is my favorite image in computer art. The random and repetitive animation is based on patterns that it erases and recreates each time. The random pauses in the flow and the subsequent motion wiping each texture and recreating it result in a unique animation.


*Start and stop animation: press ‘Q’
*Save image: press 'W' to save the current image as a PNG.

----------------------------------------------------------------

metadata.name: Pegs In Motion #465
metadata.description:
Pegs In Motion adds a twist to the original PEGS project by adding animation, rotating the pegs to make the string loop around the grid and bring the artwork alive. Forever limited to 500 unique editions on the Tezos blockchain.

Taking inspiration from work by Karl Gerstner, Armin Hofmann, Nick Kuder and Dmitri Cherniak, Pegs In Motion explores the limits of constrained algorithmic variation. Based on the simple, playful idea of wrapping a string across a board of pegs, it shows how endless possibilities can be achieved with just a basic set of rules and a few primary colors. When done right, generative art challenges us to answer fundamental questions around creativity, beauty, and life itself.

metadata.name: dg5721() #7
metadata.description:
A tiny neural network with 5721 neurons, that tries to imitate human handwriting by generating new hallucinated digits in real-time.

It can generate these digits at any resolution and will invent its own ways to fill the gaps.

- Press <SPACE> or click to toggle the infinite latent space exploration.
- Press <S> to save the current frame as PNG at the current screen resolution x2.

It can be installed to work offline (Install button in the URL bar in Chrome or "Add to Home screen" on iOS)

As of 2021, this artwork requires a fast computer or mobile phone.

metadata.name: Automata Monads #57
metadata.description:
“In the end, every system that follows definite rules can be thought of as a cellular automaton.”
Stephen Wolfram

Our thoughts and our universe consist of systems that may seem chaotic but fundamentally operate according to specific rules. Cellular automata are a model where these rules come to life in a simple yet profound way. Each cell evolves solely based on its neighboring cells, following a deterministic process. This evolutionary progression transforms an initially simple order into complex and mesmerizing patterns over time. Just like in nature, every small interaction is part of a grand transformation. The universe of cellular automata is a dynamic structure that follows rules yet remains full of surprises.  

This collection was created to explore the aesthetic and mathematical beauty of cellular automata. Each piece visualizes how a complex order emerges from simple rules. The interactions between colors, forms, and structures reveal the depth and power of the system's rules. Inspired by iconic collections such as "RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton," my goal with this project is to bring together the evolutionary beauty of fundamental rules in both natural and artificial systems and to open a window into the essence of these models through an interactive approach.

[R] Cam mode / Reset to start point
[W] Forward move
[S] Backward move
[A] Left move
[D] Right move
[Hold Shift] Fast move
[ESC] Disable pointer lock
———————————————————
[Q] Start and stop animation
[E] Fullscreen mode
[Z] Save image as a PNG
* Interactive mode works best on a new window.

metadata.name: ∿∿Hz∿∿ #24
metadata.description:
"∿∿Hz∿∿" is a generative artwork that explores the hidden beauty of wave mechanics through digital abstraction. Each strand exists as an autonomous entity, dancing to the mathematical rhythm of sine waves while maintaining its own unique signature of amplitude, frequency, and motion.

The dynamic visualization combines randomized parameters with precise mathematical foundations to create a continuously evolving system. The result is a composition where bright oscillating forms move against a dark background, creating an ever-changing visual study of wave behavior and harmonics.
